In the midst of all that,

28:36.160 --> 28:48.793
well,

28:36.160 --> 28:48.793
again, you have to understand the mood at the time. 
We were deep in the midst of what I call the age of

28:50.090 --> 28:56.077
relevance. Everything that you did had to be 
relevant. It had to serve mankind in a very direct

29:00.223 --> 29:03.246
way. Our students, incidentally, respected that

29:04.908 --> 29:09.915
viewpoint. There was no joy of learning. There was 
no desire to learn anything just for the fun of

29:12.558 --> 29:17.464
learning it. It had to be relevant to something. It 
had to be directly applicable. And the

29:23.539 --> 29:30.427
engineering students of that day, they wanted to 
know just what they needed to know to be

29:23.539 --> 29:30.427
successful. No more, no less, but just what they 
needed. You still see some tinges of that today,

29:35.032 --> 29:43.421
but it's much diminished than what it was. Well, 
the same thing applied to research. And one heard

29:47.498 --> 29:58.493
that during those days, you know, if we can put a man 
on the moon, surely to God we can do blah, blah,

29:47.498 --> 29:58.493
blah. And at that point, in that day and age,

29:59.053 --> 30:15.936
the problems of the urban

